                <h1>Fascinating Facts About Cleopatra: The Last Pharaoh</h1>
                <p>Cleopatra VII, the last Pharaoh of Egypt, was a remarkable figure known for her intelligence, political savvy, and beauty. Born in 69 BC, she was the first in her family to learn the Egyptian language. Cleopatra famously had relationships with Julius Caesar and Mark Antony, significantly influencing Roman politics before her tragic death in 30 BC.</p>
